abstract: Gregor Sailer traveled the globe photographing Potemkin villages, architectural landscapes that are clones, impostors or frauds.
snippet: Gregor Sailer traveled the globe photographing Potemkin villages, architectural landscapes that are clones, impostors or frauds.
lead_paragraph: ARLES, France — The neighborhood looks unremarkable, if a little unkempt: a dollar store, a laundromat, a fashion business with a few other sidelines (“All cellphone bills paid here”). The sky is heavy, the color of pewter; snow blankets the sidewalk. The adverts for the New York Lottery in the grocery store windows are a giveaway. But something is off. What district of New York City is one story high? And can those be pine trees in the background?

headline_main: A World Tour of Fake Places That Fool the Eye

abstract: Was Dean Skelos, the former leader of the New York State Senate, a doting father and devoted lawmaker, or a threatening politician? Closing arguments offer differing views.
snippet: Was Dean Skelos, the former leader of the New York State Senate, a doting father and devoted lawmaker, or a threatening politician? Closing arguments offer differing views.
lead_paragraph: The lawyers in the four-week corruption retrial of Dean G. Skelos, the once-powerful former leader of the New York State Senate, have not agreed on much, but they at least had seemed to agree that Mr. Skelos was devoted to his son.

abstract: The leader of one of the biggest Buddhist organizations in the West steps aside after allegations of sexual abuse, leaving followers reeling.
snippet: The leader of one of the biggest Buddhist organizations in the West steps aside after allegations of sexual abuse, leaving followers reeling.
lead_paragraph: In a shrine on the sixth floor of a Manhattan office building, a photo of a man in golden robes hangs above an altar. Another photo of him sits upon a throne.

headline_main: The ‘King’ of Shambhala Buddhism Is Undone by Abuse Report
headline_print_headline: Women Allege Abuse, and a Buddhist ‘King’ Falls

abstract: Croatia, in their third straight game that went to extra time, rode its resiliency to a semifinal win and ended England’s effervescent run in this tournament.
snippet: Croatia, in their third straight game that went to extra time, rode its resiliency to a semifinal win and ended England’s effervescent run in this tournament.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Their legs had stopped working long before the end. Their muscles ached, their lungs heaved, their bodies creaked and groaned. Croatia’s players had hit their limits and traveled beyond them, yet again. They had drained themselves of adrenaline. They had passed deep into the red, into the pain.

abstract: New York has the lowest rate of organ donor registration in the country. Thousands languish on wait lists, and hundreds needlessly die every year.
snippet: New York has the lowest rate of organ donor registration in the country. Thousands languish on wait lists, and hundreds needlessly die every year.
lead_paragraph: Kehinde Majekodumi does not look desperately ill. A vibrant 24-year-old, she bears little outward sign except a scar beneath her collarbone where a catheter was once inserted.

abstract: In representing the porn star Stormy Daniels, the lawyer thinks he can bring down a president — one cable-news appearance at a time.
snippet: In representing the porn star Stormy Daniels, the lawyer thinks he can bring down a president — one cable-news appearance at a time.
lead_paragraph: The attorney Michael Avenatti stands just under six feet tall, with blatant blue eyes and thinning hair he shaves down to stubble, exposing the crumpled vein at his left temple. Before February, when he agreed to represent Stephanie Clifford — the pornographic film performer better known as Stormy Daniels — in her legal battle with the president of the United States, Avenatti was in the best shape of his life: 185 pounds, 9 percent body fat. The ever-expanding pressures of the case have meant less time at the gym, and in recent months he has lost some muscle weight. But his cheeks and chin remain Cubist in their geometry, and in motion, head lowered and shoulders hunched, he still has the bearing of a light-heavyweight brawler.

headline_main: The Fast and Furious Michael Avenatti

abstract: This iteration of the comic series, starting in November, will take cues from TV’s “Riverdale,” and a new Betty & Veronica series is on tap for December.
snippet: This iteration of the comic series, starting in November, will take cues from TV’s “Riverdale,” and a new Betty & Veronica series is on tap for December.
lead_paragraph: Archie Andrews, the seemingly eternal redhead from Riverdale, and his friends will be getting new creative teams later this year that will take some cues from the CW’s “Riverdale” television series and explore new terrain for the characters.
